;; AIF+ argument model of the NPT paper
;;
;; Purpose: scratch work to understand what the paper is doing as a
;; communication act, identify structural weaknesses, and decide what
;; to keep, cut, or integrate properly (especially the role-based reanalysis).
;;
;; Node types:
;;   :I-node  — information node (proposition, claim, datum)
;;   :RA-node — inference scheme (support relation between I-nodes)
;;   :CA-node — conflict scheme (attack relation between I-nodes)
;;   :PA-node — preference scheme (priority between competing claims)
;;
;; Convention: IDs use section numbers to trace back to paper structure.
;; Edge :type is one of :support, :attack, :preference, :evidence, :presupposition

{:model/id :npt-paper-argument
 :model/purpose "Structural analysis of paper's argument for coherence checking"

