  ;;
  ;; It does NOT appear in:
  ;;   - Pattern presentations (4.1.1) — no roles named per pattern
  ;;   - Logic model description — no role annotations
  ;;   - The tier distinction argument — roles could ground this but don't
  ;;   - Ostrom connection — roles map to Ostrom's "recognised rights to organise"
  ;;
  ;; The role analysis produces three genuinely new claims:
  ;;   (a) Coordination complexity gradient
  ;;   (b) Role overload as mechanism of absorbed input
  ;;   (c) Specific absent roles (esp. EV_analyse, ORCA support)
  ;; But (a) gets one paragraph, (b) gets one sentence, (c) doesn't appear at all.

  {:id :CA-role-disconnect
   :type :CA-node
